# ITU BLG202 - Numerical Methods in Computer Engineering

This repository contains coursework, assignments, and projects for the **BLG 202 - Numerical Methods in Computer Engineering** course at Istanbul Technical University (ITU). The course focuses on numerical techniques used in scientific and engineering computations, implemented using programming.

## Contents
- **Assignments:** Problem-solving exercises covering various numerical methods.
- **Projects:** Larger applications demonstrating numerical techniques in real-world scenarios.
- **Lecture Notes & Examples:** Supplementary materials to reinforce key concepts.

## Topics Covered
- Root Finding Methods (Bisection, Newton-Raphson, Secant Method)
- Interpolation and Curve Fitting
- Numerical Differentiation and Integration
- Systems of Linear Equations (Gaussian Elimination, LU Decomposition)
- Eigenvalue Problems
- Ordinary Differential Equations (Eulerâ€™s Method, Runge-Kutta Methods)
- Error Analysis and Stability

# Notes
- The code follows best practices for numerical computing and algorithm implementation.
- No external libraries are used unless explicitly required.
- Academic integrity is maintained in all submissions.

